Nmap is a common and popular scanning and enumeration tool, with different ways to utilize it, below are a few of some commands:

nmap <IP> -F -->> Fast scan
nmap <IP> -A -->> performs everything.
nmap <IP> -T4 --> Increases the threads, which is the intensity, th lower the number the less intrusive it is, which can be useful when trying to scan while undetected.
namp <IP> -Pn 
nmap <IP> -Pc 
